Package: SNIRF2BIDS
Title: Converts SNIRF Files to BIDS-Compliant Datasets
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Raphael", "Lorenz-de Laigue", , "raphael.lorenz-de-laigue@uni-tuebingen.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    person("Jennifer", "Svaldi", , "jennifer.svaldi@uni-tuebingen.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    person("Philipp", "Schroeder", , "philipp.schroeder@uni-tuebingen.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a graphical user interface (GUI) to convert raw functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) recordings in SNIRF format into BIDS-compliant datasets. 
     The package interfaces with the Python-based MNE-BIDS library via 'reticulate', using the write_raw_bids function for data conversion. 
     On first use, a dedicated Miniconda environment is automatically installed and configured with all required dependencies (e.g., 'mne', 'mne-bids'), ensuring a reproducible and self-contained workflow. 
     The environment is installed once, if not already detected locally, and reused in subsequent sessions.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.1)
Imports: shiny, shinyFiles, reticulate, bslib, here, tidyr, bslib, here, DT, stringr, purrr, dplyr, BiocManager, rhdf5, datamods, shinyjs, magrittr
